author: Spencer Jakab
title: Wal-Mart’s Valuation Has Room to Grow
text:
Like certain baseball players, Wal-Mart Stores Inc. now needs an asterisk next to its claim to fame.
That isn’t because it did anything untoward in making more revenue than its peers—Wal-Mart’s is 4½ times that of its closest competitor—but because it has been bumped down to No. 2 on another important measure.
